element.name: Glendougal's Little Hiding Hole by Orangetigerprawn, Traditional Cache (3/3.5)
element.long-description:
Traditional small cache located near Barnageeragh beach between Skerries and Balbriggan. Nice views northwards on a clear day.
Probably not the driest cache to be doing if the tide is high with a strong easterly breeze.
element.encoded-hints: You know when you're searching for a cache in a forest and the hint says tree? Well here it's "rock."
